                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_dæsny" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>dæsny</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>dæsni</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>искусный</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>skillfull</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>мастер</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>master</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>знаток</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>expert</q></tr></sense></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>знахарь</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>healer</q></tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в старом языке также</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">in old language also</note></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>dæsny færsyn</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>знахарствовать</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>to be a healer</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ворожить</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>tell fortunes</q></tr></sense></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>dæsniad</orth><form type="variant"><orth>dæsnyʒinad</orth></form></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>искусство</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>art</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>мастерство</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>skill</q></tr></sense></sense></re><exampleGrp><example><quote>xærdgæjæ dæsny</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>искусный (в вышивании) канителью</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>a good hand at needlework with gold twisted thread</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>57</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>dæsny wydysty mæsyg amajynmæ, æmæ sæm ʒævgar pajda cydī ūcy dæsniadæj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>они были искусны строить башни, и благодаря этому мастерству им шли немалые заработки</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>they were skilled at building towers, and they received considerable earnings because of thanks this skill</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>95</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>qæwy īw acærgægomaw ūs dæsny wydi</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>в ауле была одна пожилая женщина знахарка</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>there was one elderly healer woman in the aul</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>176</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>dæw dær, mæ lymæn, dæsny nal ysʒæbæx kænʒæn</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>и тебя, приятель, не вылечит больше знахарь</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>and you, buddy, will no longer be cured by the healer</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>101</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>ʒorunmæ dæsni æj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>говорить он мастер</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>he is a master at speaking</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>77</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>fæcæj næ kizgæ dæsni ǧæwagæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>наша дочка нуждается в знахаре</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>our daughter needs a healer</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>91</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>dæsny jæxīcæn næ zony</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>знахарь для себя не умеет (гадать)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the healer does not know how (to tell fortunes) for himself</q></tr><bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">поговорка</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">saying</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>rajsta ta dæsny Biganon aǧ˳yvzæ æmæ jæ ærtykkag xatt bīræ fezmæsta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>взяла опять знахарка Биганон стакан и в третий раз долго в нем мешала</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the healer Biganon took the glass again and for the third time stirred something in it for a long time</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Arsen"/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>су zonys dæsny ʒinadæj?</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>какое мастерство ты знаешь?</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>what skill do you know?</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>76</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>dæsnyʒinad k˳yrd k˳yndyl ах˳уr kæny</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>мастерству кузнец учится у кузнеца</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the blacksmith learns the skills from the blacksmith</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 200</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>xærdgæjæ dæsny</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>искусный (в вышивании) канителью</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>a good hand at needlework with gold twisted thread</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>57</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>dæsny wydysty mæsyg amajynmæ, æmæ sæm ʒævgar pajda cydī ūcy dæsniadæj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>они были искусны строить башни, и благодаря этому мастерству им шли немалые заработки</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>they were skilled at building towers, and they received considerable earnings because of thanks this skill</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>95</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>qæwy īw acærgægomaw ūs dæsny wydi</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>в ауле была одна пожилая женщина знахарка</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>there was one elderly healer woman in the aul</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>176</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>dæw dær, mæ lymæn, dæsny nal ysʒæbæx kænʒæn</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>и тебя, приятель, не вылечит больше знахарь</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>and you, buddy, will no longer be cured by the healer</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>101</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>ʒorunmæ dæsni æj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>говорить он мастер</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>he is a master at speaking</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>77</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>fæcæj næ kizgæ dæsni ǧæwagæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>наша дочка нуждается в знахаре</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>our daughter needs a healer</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>91</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>dæsny jæxīcæn næ zony</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>знахарь для себя не умеет (гадать)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the healer does not know how (to tell fortunes) for himself</q></tr><bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">поговорка</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">saying</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>rajsta ta dæsny Biganon aǧ˳yvzæ æmæ jæ ærtykkag xatt bīræ fezmæsta</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>взяла опять знахарка Биганон стакан и в третий раз долго в нем мешала</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the healer Biganon took the glass again and for the third time stirred something in it for a long time</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Arsen"/><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>су zonys dæsny ʒinadæj?</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>какое мастерство ты знаешь?</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>what skill do you know?</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>76</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>dæsnyʒinad k˳yrd k˳yndyl ах˳уr kæny</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>мастерству кузнец учится у кузнеца</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the blacksmith learns the skills from the blacksmith</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 200</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Отвечает <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>dakṣiṇa-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>dašina-</w></mentioned>. Основа *%ideks%i- выступает в индоевропейских языках в двух тесно связанных между собою значениях: с одной стороны, ‘правый’ (→ ‘правая рука’, ‘правая сторона’, ‘юг’), с другой — ‘искусный’, ‘удачный’, ‘благоприятный’ и пр. Известно, что ‘правая сторона’ с давних пор ассоциируется со счастьем, удачей, искусством, а ‘левая’ — с несчастьем, неудачей, неловкостью („правая рука“ = „искусная рука“). В осетинском значение ‘правый’, ‘правая рука’ отсутствует (см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_raxīz"/>). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>dašn</w> <gloss><q>справа</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>δšny</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (о ветре)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (about wind)</note> <gloss><q>благоприятный</q></gloss></mentioned> (а не „juste“, как переводит %sBenveniste%s: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_TSP"/><biblScope>%i3%i 204</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>dašina-</w> <gloss><q>правый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/> <gloss><q>правая сторона</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>dakṣiṇa-</w> <gloss><q>искусный</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>ловкий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>правый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>правосторонний</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>южный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>благоприятный</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/> <w>деснъ</w> <gloss><q>правый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="cu"><w>десница</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/> <w>desżinė́</w> <gloss><q>правая рука</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>δεξιός</w> <gloss><q>искусный</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>ловкий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>умный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>правый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>справа находящийся</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>благоприятный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>счастливый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>δεξιότης</w> <gloss><q>искусство</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>мастерство</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>dæsniad</w></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>dexter</w> <gloss><q>правый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/> <gloss><q>справа находящийся</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/> <gloss><q>благоприятный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/> <gloss><q>приносящий счастье</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/> <gloss><q>ловкий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/> <gloss><q>искусный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>dexteritas</w> <gloss><q>ловкость</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/> <gloss><q>искусство</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Для значения ‘знахарь’ ср. <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/> <w>usta</w> <gloss><q>искусный</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><w/> <gloss><q>знахарь</q></gloss></mentioned>, . <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>kṣ</w></mentioned> в осетинском отвечает обычно %ixs%i (см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_rūxs"/> ‘свет’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xsæv"/> ‘ночь’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xsyr"/> ‘молоко’ и др.); однако ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syd"/> ‘голод’ = <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>kṣudh-</w></mentioned>. %sВаilеу%s (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>8</biblScope></bibl>) возводит %idæsny%i к *%idastya%i, что фонетически мало вероятно.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>47, 77, 82</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It corresponds to <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>dakṣiṇa-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>dašina-</w></mentioned>. The stem *%ideks%i- has two closely related meanings in Indo-European languages: on the one hand, ‘right’ (→ ‘right hand’, ‘right side’, ‘south’), on the other — ‘skillfull’, ‘lucky’, ‘prosperous’ etc. It is known that ‘right side’ has been associated with happiness, luck, art for a long time and ‘left side’ — with misfortune, bad luck, awkwardness (“right hand” = “skilled hand”). The meaning ‘right’, ‘right side’ lacks in the Ossetic language (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_raxīz"/>). Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/> <w>dašn</w> <gloss><q>rightward</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/> <w>δšny</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (о ветре)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (about wind)</note> <gloss><q>prosperous</q></gloss></mentioned> (and not “juste”, as translates %sBenveniste%s: <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_TSP"/><biblScope>%i3%i 204</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>dašina-</w> <gloss><q>right</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/> <gloss><q>right side</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>dakṣiṇa-</w> <gloss><q>skillfull</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>dexterous</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>right</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>right sided</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>southern</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>prosperous</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/> <w>desnъ</w> <gloss><q>right</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="cu"><w>desnitsa</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/> <w>desżinė́</w> <gloss><q>right hand</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>δεξιός</w> <gloss><q>skillfull</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>dexterous</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>clever</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>right</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>situated on the right</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>prosperous</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>happy</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>δεξιότης</w> <gloss><q>art</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>skill</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>dæsniad</w></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>dexter</w> <gloss><q>right</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/> <gloss><q>situated on the right</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/> <gloss><q>prosperous</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/> <gloss><q>bringing happiness</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/> <gloss><q>dexterous</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/> <gloss><q>skillfull</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>dexteritas</w> <gloss><q>skill</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/> <gloss><q>art</q></gloss></mentioned>, . For the meaning ‘healer’ cf. <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/> <w>usta</w> <gloss><q>skillfull</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><w/> <gloss><q>healer</q></gloss></mentioned>, . <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>kṣ</w></mentioned> usually refers to %ixs%i in Ossetic (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_rūxs"/> ‘light’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xsæv"/> ‘night’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xsyr"/> ‘milk’ etc.); however cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syd"/> ‘hunger’ = <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>kṣudh-</w></mentioned>. %sВаilеy%s (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>8</biblScope></bibl>) traces %idæsny%i back to *%idastya%i, which is highly doubtful due to phonetic reasons.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>47, 77, 82</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>